00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:12.140
 What are the limits of the political act of the new palace of Carthage? Chapter Four of the Tunisian Constitution on Executive Power defines the powers of the President of the Republic. 

00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:21.260
 The most important of these powers: - Representation of the state and control of public policies in the areas of defense, foreign relations and national security 

00:00:21.940 --> 00:00:31.380
 - Dissolution of the House of Representatives in cases provided by the Constitution - the Presidency of the Supreme Command of the Armed Forces - Presidency of the National Security Council 

00:00:31.780 --> 00:00:40.880
 The President is also authorized to: - Declare war and conclude peace after the approval of the House of Representatives - and take the measures required by exceptional cases 

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:55.640
 As well as appointments and exemptions in senior military, diplomatic and national security positions after consultation with the Prime Minister 

00:00:56.300 --> 00:01:11.620
 Among the powers are also: - Appointment of the Governor of the Central Bank at the proposal of the Prime Minister - Ratification of treaties and permission to publish them - as well as the awarding of decorations and special amnesty - and the appointment of the Mufti of the Republic 

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:31.240
 The powers of the Constitution are drawn up by a Constituent Assembly directly representing the people, and specialists agree that these powers interact in a balanced and integrated relationship with the legislative and judicial authorities. However, this does not overlook the enormous challenges awaiting the new president. 

00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:40.620
 Politically, the Tunisian people demand: - To consolidate gains in rights and freedoms and to resist tyranny and the rule of total authoritarianism. 

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:49.900
 - Maintaining the peaceful course of the democratic transition process - supporting the political process and overcoming the stage of shipping and polarization 

00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:58.600
 Amnon, Tunisians wait for the new leader: - Stabilize stability and security and end the manifestations of violence that seemed strange to them. 

00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:10.660
 To ensure this, experts emphasize the need to: - Develop a clear strategy to combat terrorism - Reform and modernization of the security and military system to ensure and strengthen the power of the state 

00:02:11.080 --> 00:02:23.000
 The most important economic and social challenges are: - To remedy the economic downturn, which was evident in the budget deficit, trade deficit, high prices and unemployment 

00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:38.560
 - Restoring the confidence of local and foreign investors, which has declined by 24 percent in the past two years. - Structuring the mechanisms of production and development and ensuring their equality between all the regions of the country. 

00:02:39.980 --> 00:02:48.660
 Many implications in the current Tunisian situation, the election wedding fold in its internal context a stage of political and security fluctuations, 

00:02:49.060 --> 00:02:58.480
 On the regional level, he demonstrates that the experience of democracy, despite its difficulties and its resurgence, remains viable in the Arab world. 

